[2] Ukraine
Date: Mon 12 Dec 2011
Source: Kyiv Post, Interfax Ukraine [edited]
http: //www.kyivpost.com/news/nation/detail/118781/

Doctors concerned about outbreak of measles in Ukraine
------------------------------------------------------
Up to 500 people in Ukraine may contract measles by the end of this
year, Ukrainian First Deputy Health Minister Raisa Moiseyenko has
said.

"Some 193 cases were recorded as of 1 Nov 2011, but the number of
patients currently seen in western Ukraine is growing. At the end of
the year, we could have 500 such cases [of measles]," she said at a
press conference in Kyiv on Monday [12 Dec 2011].

At the same time, Moiseyenko noted that anti-epidemic and medical
activities were carried out in the Lviv and Ivano-Frankivsk regions
properly and in full.

According to a press release distributed to reporters, the latest
figures of the WHO Regional Office for Europe, over 30 000 cases of
measles have been reported in 29 countries in Europe since January
2011.

