[3] Angola (Zaire)
Date: Wed 14 Dec 2011
Source: Angop Sante, AngolaPress [In French, trans. & edited by
mod.CP]
http://www.portalanop.co.ao/motix/fr_fr/noticias/saude/2011/11/50/epidemie-rougeole-est-sous-controle-affirment-les-autorites-sanitaires,b0112903-dc52-4ed1-ad5d-47437d360c39.html

Measles epidemic under control
------------------------------
The health authorities in the twn of Mbanza Kongo, the capital of
Zaire province de, declared on Tuesday [13 Dec 2011] that the measles
epidemic which had affected the town since August was now under
control. The outbreak had been responsible for 8 deaths.

In a statement to Angop Manuel Salvado, Director of the Infectious
Disease Department of the Municipal Hospitaal of Mbanza Kongo, stated
that 379 measles cases had been admitted since the beginning of
August, 262 of whom were children under 5 years old.

In view of this situation the hospital had been obliged to transfer
patients with other illnesses to the Provincial Hospital, and to
reserve a ward for the treatment of measles patients. At the present
time 23 measles patients, comprising 2 adults and 21 children, are
receiving treatment.

