[6] Ecuador (Amazona)
Date: Thu 15 Dec 2011
Source: Vistazo.com [In Spanish, trans. Corr SB, edited]
http://www.vistazo.com/webpages/pais/?id=18287

Outbreak of Measles in a community of Pastaza (Amazona, Equador)
-----------------------------------------------------------------
The Health authorities have declared a quarantine area around Kapawi.
At least 300 indigenous Achuar have not been able to move from their
town [Kapawi] to other communities. Carlos Vimos, Head of Epidemology
in Pastaza says that those people living in Kapawi cannot leave to go
to Puyo or move to other communities until the infectious period for
measles is ended.

6 cases have been registered: 4 adults and 2 children

